<p>The <a href="https://www.philosophie.lmu.de/mcmp/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Munich Center for Mathematical Philosophy</a> (MCMP) and the <a href="https://badw.de/die-akademie.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bavarian Academy of Sciences and Humanities</a> (BAdW) are launching a joint project to digitize and place online the complete works of <a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/carnap/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rudolf Carnap</a>.<span id="more-55944"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class=" wp-image-55945 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/carnap-digital-duo-1024x515.jpg" alt="" width="795" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/carnap-digital-duo-1024x515.jpg 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/carnap-digital-duo-300x151.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/carnap-digital-duo-768x386.jpg 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/carnap-digital-duo-1536x772.jpg 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/carnap-digital-duo-2048x1030.jpg 2048w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/carnap-digital-duo-400x201.jpg 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /></p>
<p>Led by <a href="https://www.philosophie.lmu.de/en/directory-of-persons/contact-page/hannes-leitgeb-4769c328.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hannes Leitgeb</a> and <a href="http://www.stephanhartmann.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stephan Hartmann</a> (LMU Munich) together with <a href="https://eckhartarnold.de/EN/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eckhart Arnold</a> (Bavarian Academy of Sciences and Humanities), the project, &#8220;Rudolf Carnap Digital,&#8221; will run for 25 years under the German <a href="https://www.akademienunion.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Academies’ Programme</a>.</p>
<p>According to Professor Hartmann, the project</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><em>will produce the first complete scholarly edition of Carnap’s oeuvre, covering both his published writings and an extensive, largely inaccessible archive: over 100,000 manuscript pages, seven decades of diaries, and nearly 10,000 letters. These materials will be made available through three interconnected outputs: a full facsimile archive, a digital critical edition, and a bilingual study edition, all published open access.</em></p>
<p>Additionally, an open-access platform is being developed that will make Carnap&#8217;s &#8220;logical deductions available as digital mathematical objects,&#8221; according to the BAdW announcement of the project <a href="https://badw.de/die-akademie/presse/pressemitteilungen/pm-einzelartikel/detail/drei-neue-projekte-der-badw-im-akademienprogramm.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/12/16/the-complete-carnap-online-and-open-access/">The Complete Carnap: Online and Open-Access</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>